			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Kelel wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">I am a little peeved about the maping of arrows. Why is it that we have to jockey around to get a good position to make good on our archery?
<br />
...
<br />
 I have never /feedback is that what you do to report a problem or just for game feedback "arrow maping"? If that is the case i will /feedback once a day to argue this point and i hope others will do the same.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
First, I have no problem with the fact that a bunch of melee attackers surrounding my target can block my shot <span style="font-weight: bold">When they obstruct the majority of my target</span>.  In such a case I can just chalk it up to, I can't hit him without hitting someone else with that particular shot.  (How many times as a young archer did you 'graze' some other mob and bring them in by accident?  Giant rats invisibly 'stand' as tall as wood elves.  I learned that long ago, the hard way.)
<br />

<br />
Second, when my target is an ogre and the only people meleeing him are the size of gnomes, everything I'd normally want to aim for (torso, head, etc) is in plain view and I should be able to hit that target with little difficulty.
<br />

<br />
What kind of archery master am I if I can't hit a hill giant?  He's <span style="font-style: italic">bigger</span> than the broad side of a barn!
<br />

<br />
I have, over the course of time, learned a number of elements about LOS in Everquest, and I find it to be an interesting test to overcome.  But the fact that it stands in the way of some of my best high end game damage, I have to say, I'm disappointed in it.
<br />

<br />
As for / commands for issues in the game.
<br />

<br />
/feedback is a slow moving 'suggestion box' or 'kudos' spot.
<br />

<br />
/bug generates a log to be reviewed by game developers for things that don't work the way they are intended.
<br />

<br />
/petition is used to request assistance in game from Guides and Customer Service personnel.
<br />

<br />
If you're going to put information in about these sorts of issues.  I would suggest producing a detailed description to type into a /bug report and a /feedback.
<br />

<br />
The feedback will not be handled by the developers right away, a significant presence there may prompt some further 'looking into the matter'
<br />

<br />
The bug reports will be checked by development staff more readily, but may not result in changes unless higher ups say "This needs to be fixed" which may take a lot of bug and feedback reports.
<br />

<br />
Petitions will get you a response in game from Guides and Customer Support Reps.  Unfortunately, these people have no power over developers and can only be passed along as bug reports and feedback.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=852643" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dharisk</a>
<br />
Ranger of Tunare (deity and server)</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
