			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My experiences are:
<br />

<br />
Players: sometimes block my shooting, but not usually.  Seasoned players know that when you have an AM3 Ranger in the party, shrink all the melees to help.
<br />

<br />
Pets: This is a tricky one.  Enchanter, Wizzy and Mage pets ALWAYS block my shots if they are in my LoS, others pets do NOT.  Go figure.
<br />

<br />
NPC's: Will ALWAYS get in the way, and if they were mezzed will not be anymore.  Seasoned players know to separate grouped mobs with a AM3 Ranger in the party.
<br />

<br />
Victims (in LDoN): If you shoot too close to them or over top of them, you WILL hit them, even though the arrow is flying 3 feet above them.  Go figure.
<br />

<br />
Walls: Another tricky one. If you shoot at the mob from the SIDE when he is on a wall you will hit about 50% of the time.  Try and hit him from straight on and you will always miss.
<br />

<br />
Uneven terrain: You will see your arrows hitting the ground.  There are numerous terrain bugs that will cause gorunded arrows.  Just move to a better spot.
<br />

<br />
Best spot:  I have found the sweet spot to be 45 degrees off the the left or right from the FRONT of the mob.  If you can be about twice the mob's height above him (with SOE or DMF, or up on a wall) you will hit the best, and rarely will something get in the way because you are sniping from above.  I have found that shooting from the back yeilds lower hits, even though the mob cannot technically have a chance at defending.  Kinda funny how a big summoned defender rock mob can dodge a doggone arrow.  Go figure.
<br />

<br />
Now here is the kicker....why is it that at level 65 with an Archery skill mod bow, over 100 AA's, etc that according to my parse file I am only 66% accurate with my dam bow?  Make a pally or a warrior only 66% effective with their melee, and a pure caster fizzle 33% of the time and see how fast they would get mad!  Go figure.
<br />

<br />
I say they should raise a Ranger's Archery ability to 250.  Plain and simple.
<br />

<br />
Opinions will vary.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=640849" target="_blank" class="postlink">Hunter Devross Stormfury</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.forgottenlegion.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">&lt;Forgotten Legion&gt;</a>
<br />
&lt;    Bristlebane    &gt;</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
