				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've found that since Nov. 5th, LoS is practically meaningless.  What we really need to consider is LoF.  Huh??, you say; what in the world is LoF??  Well, it's Line of Feet.  If your feet cans 'see' the mob's feet and you're withing range; you're gonna score.  After reading the screams of many rangers and much experimentation since the Nov 5th patch; this is the conclusion I have come to.  This is why levitation or standing on something helps our accuracy.  I mention Nov. 5th because that is when I really started to have severe LoS issues in non-raiding situations.
<br />

<br />

<br />
